benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/admin/queues - Get queues entries

covered: Valid Request: Multiple scenarios (TC01-TC10, TC23) validate successful retrieval with default behavior and many combinations of query parameters (accountId, queueName, serviceName, date range, and flag combinations).
Empty Response: TC11 and TC29 cover empty-database and filter-excludes-all-data cases returning empty responses with 200.

Query Parameters: Extensive coverage of query parameter permutations including valid/invalid accountId (TC02, TC13, TC14), queueName (TC03), serviceName (TC04), minDate/maxDate (TC05, TC24, TC25), boolean flags withHistory/withInProcessing/withBusEvents/withNotifications (TC06-TC09, TC21, TC22).

Error Handling: HTTP error scenarios are covered: 400 for invalid input (TC13, TC25, TC17/TC26 sanitize attempts), 404 for account-not-found (TC14), 401 unauthorized (TC15), 500 internal error (TC30), 503 service unavailable (TC16), and 504 timeout (TC19).
Security and robustness: Injection and XSS attempts are explicitly tested (TC17, TC26).
Performance/scale: Large data volume and acceptable response time are considered (TC18).
Concurrency/resilience: Concurrent requests and retry/recovery behavior are included (TC20, TC27).
Backward compatibility & regression: Legacy defaults and regression for withHistory are included (TC21, TC22).
Content type: Default response content-type application/octet-stream is asserted in TC01 (matches acceptance criteria).
gaps: Pagination: No tests address pagination/streaming controls (page/limit/offset) or verify behavior when results are split across pages for large datasets — the large-volume test (TC18) checks performance but not pagination semantics.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control, Last-Modified) or conditional GET behavior (304 responses).
Rate Limiting / Throttling: No tests verify rate-limiting behavior (429 responses) or handling of many requests in a short burst; concurrency (TC20) exists but does not exercise throttling limits.

Authorization scope/permissions (403): Tests include 401 for missing/invalid token (TC15) but do not cover forbidden scenarios where authentication is valid but caller lacks required admin privileges (403).

Boolean parameter validation & edge cases: No tests for malformed boolean values (e.g., withHistory=notabool) or for inconsistent combinations (e.g., withHistory=false together with flags that imply history), nor for minDate > maxDate validation.

Response stream/content validation: Acceptance criteria require an octet-stream of queue entries; tests assert content-type but do not validate the stream format/decodability, schema, or max payload chunking.
Header/metadata checks: No tests asserting other important response headers (Content-Length, Transfer-Encoding) or that the API produces application/octet-stream consistently across scenarios.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests: verify page/limit/offset (or cursor) parameters, boundary conditions (first/last page), and behavior when page size is larger/smaller than dataset. Include correctness of total counts or paging metadata if applicable.
Add caching tests: assert presence and correctness of Cache-Control, ETag, and Last-Modified headers; test conditional requests (If-None-Match / If-Modified-Since) and expected 304 responses.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests: simulate bursts of requests to check for 429 responses and graceful retry behavior (Retry-After).
Add authorization scope tests: include scenarios where authentication is valid but the caller lacks admin privileges to ensure 403 Forbidden is returned and meaningful error messages are provided.
Add boolean and parameter validation edge-case tests: malformed booleans, unsupported parameter values, and cross-parameter validation (e.g., minDate > maxDate) should return clear 4xx errors.

Validate response payload format and stream decoding: tests should deserialize the octet-stream, validate the queue entry schema, and verify behavior for very large streamed payloads (chunking, memory).
Include header/metadata assertions across scenarios: Content-Type (already present in TC01), Content-Length or Transfer-Encoding, and any custom headers the API guarantees.
Extend performance tests to cover pagination performance (not just full-volume retrieval) and capture SLA metrics; include rate-limiting interaction with performance.
